content_chunks.content: This digital course is designed to provide knowledge and practical experience in three levels (basic, intermediate and advanced) on the transformative potential of blockchain technology in the built environment. Students will gain insight into the fundamentals of blockchain, smart contracts and decentralised systems, focusing on their applications in improving transparency, efficiency and trust in the built environment. Key topics include BIM and smart asset management, payment and project management, procurement and supply chain management, sustainable practices through tokenisation. By the end of the course, students will be able to evaluate and implement blockchain solutions tailored to the challenges and opportunities of the built environment.

Blockchain technology for built environment transparency and efficiency - this course delivers comprehensive expertise in distributed ledger systems, smart contracts, and decentralized applications for construction and real estate. Students gain practical skills in implementing blockchain solutions for BIM integration, smart asset management, automated payment systems, and supply chain transparency. The curriculum covers tokenization for sustainable building practices, cryptographic security protocols, and consensus mechanisms tailored to infrastructure projects. Graduates emerge equipped to develop blockchain-based platforms that enhance trust, reduce fraud, and optimize resource allocation in construction projects, enabling next-generation digital transformation in the built environment sector.
